data.title: Building Permits & Land Use Review
data.text:
Inspections must now be scheduled through the Online Permit Portal .

Scheduling requirements and tips

Please schedule inspections within the next five (5) business days. This reduces the need for cancelations and keeps inspections on schedule.

You will need to set up a portal account using your specific access code provided. Once this code is entered, you will select the permit needing an inspection.

Can't find your access code? Call us at 360.753.8314.

The online system allows you to choose AM or PM. If you need a more exact timeframe, please call 360.753.8314 at 8 a.m. on the morning of your inspection.

You can view your scheduled inspections and get status updates in the Online Permit Portal .

Before you call, visit our Online Permit Center and ensure all...

Required permits were issued.

Permits are signed off.

Permits are paid in full.

Call 360.753.8314 to request a final inspection. Staff will...

Verify all permits were issued and paid.

Contact you within 24 hours if there are outstanding fees. You must call to reschedule, once all fees are paid.

Final inspection scheduling

The inspector will determine if a pre-final inspection is required.

You will be contacted within 48 hours to schedule an inspection or informed why an inspection cannot be scheduled.

On the day of final inspection you will either be...

Approved - A certificate of occupancy will be available for download no later than 5 p.m.

Denied - Cause and actions required will be available no later than 5 p.m.
